🧠 OS Concept 1: System Call Flow (Deep Understanding)

You already know system calls.

Now let’s see:

👉 what actually happens internally.

1️⃣ Flow of System Call

Example:

read(file)
Step-by-Step
1️⃣ User Mode

Program runs normally.

2️⃣ System Call Invoked

Trap instruction executed.

CPU switches:

User Mode → Kernel Mode
3️⃣ Kernel Executes

OS accesses:

file system
disk
memory
4️⃣ Return to User Mode

Data returned to program.

🧠 Real-World Analogy

Student asks office for document.

Student → User mode
Office → Kernel mode
Request → System call
